cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an end-to-end algorithm that optimizes and learns a good metric given unlabeled trajectories using sequence autoencoders. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Autowarp is an AI-based approach that learns a warping distance from unlabeled time series data. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Measuring similarities between time series trajectories is an important problem in computer vision, and Autowarp can be applied to this domain. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Time series data is often used in social network analysis, and Autowarp can be applied to measure similarities between such data. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a flexible and differentiable family of warping metrics, which can be of interest to researchers in the field of data structures and algorithms.
